cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DB, cs.CL, cs.CR 

This paper deals with the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science, including artificial intelligence (AI), machine learning (ML), databases (DB), natural language processing (NLP), and cryptography (CR). However, the focus on probabilistic reasoning and description logics suggests that the most likely sub-category is cs.AI, followed by cs.LG (which deals with probabilistic models and learning algorithms), cs.DB (which deals with data management and querying), cs.CL (which deals with NLP and semantic analysis), and cs.CR (which deals with secure computation and privacy).
